We wish to thank the government for making life a little easier for ordinary Kenyans in 2020. We were particularly happy with the recognition of young talented engineers who locally assembled ventilators to help with mass production of cheap medical equipment.
Even though we are yet to receive an update on how many of the ventilators were bought to equip our hospitals, we are grateful for the government officials who took time out of their hectic schedules to take photos with the young talents and make another round of promises that will be actualised after the completion of the historic stadium in Kamariny.
We couldn’t also be happier with the Kenya Police Service for being on guard to remind us about observing Covid regulations. Even though corporal punishment was banned in schools before Jubilee was born, the police were on hand to take us back down memory lane, beating up those found outdoors past curfew hours.



