If you intend to buy one blade of grass to carpet the new Kisumu International Stadium, for example, kindly don’t go for nine just to make the lie good.
It is our sincere hope the government will be more responsive to the needs of ordinary citizens in 2021.
We know those who drive government policy are not ordinary people, but we ask them to walk a mile in the shoes of suffering Kenyans first before coming up with government policy, because they can afford the shoes and still have loose change to buy the priceless experience.
